Second Lady Karen Pence visited the Creative Forces music therapy program at the Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Mild Traumatic Brain Injury Clinic in Anchorage, Alaska. She met with a music therapist and observed a group music therapy session with four service members. Mrs. Pence discussed the role of music therapy in addressing their health conditions and participated in a roundtable discussion with the music therapist and hospital staff. She praised the hospital staff for recognizing the importance of creative arts therapy as a form of treatment for military service members and veterans. This visit follows Mrs. Pence's attendance at the Creative Forces Arts and Military Conference in Killeen, Texas. To stay updated on her events, follow her on Twitter at @SecondLady.